<p>I didnâ€™t even have to have to think about it before replying: News sites. And it isnâ€™t just that some news site have been slow to adopt responsive design or to redesign in general. Newly designed sites are terrible.</p>

<p>And, in particular, they arenâ€™t conducive to the way people use web sites today.</p>

<p>A large swath of readers donâ€™t go directly to news sites and enter through the front page. Twitter or Facebook, usually on some sort of mobile device, is many readersâ€™ front page now.</p>

<p>When I clicked through a link to a Baltimore Sun story, I was presented with this mess:</p>

